00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:47,839
{\an8}He or she made sure
no trace was left behind.

2
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:13,198
{\an8}But haven't the police said anything?

3
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:16,534
{\an8}Don't they have any initial findings?

4
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:21,915
{\an8}Like who's behind the group that caused
trouble at your event?

5
00:01:27,545 --> 00:01:28,505
{\an8}Well…

6
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:48,358
{\an8}They just needed money.

7
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:49,984
{\an8}Just money?

8
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:53,988
{\an8}No one will pay
for what they did to Mikoy?

9
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:55,740
{\an8}<i>Compadre…</i>

10
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,660
{\an8}I'm sorry. I hope you don't mind,

11
00:01:58,743 --> 00:02:03,998
{\an8}but I can't forget
the trauma Chiara went through

12
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:05,375
{\an8}and both our families.

13
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,132
{\an8}But for now,

14
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:15,343
{\an8}we want to move on from all of this.

15
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:17,637
{\an8}You know I can't agree, <i>compadre</i>.

16
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,890
{\an8}- I feel like, there--
- Mario.

17
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,976
{\an8}Oh, right, Viktor.

18
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:25,520
{\an8}Where's Donabel? How is she?

19
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:27,981
{\an8}And you, didn't you get shot?

20
00:02:28,064 --> 00:02:29,607
{\an8}Good thing you can move now.

21
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,818
{\an8}It wasn't life-threatening.

22
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,446
{\an8}Donabel, she's okay.

23
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:53,214
Mom will be okay.

24
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:59,637
And I'm sure she'll come back
much better and happier

25
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:02,348
after everything that happened to her.

26
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,561
Oh my, dear.

27
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:09,397
Let me talk to my in-law.

28
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:13,109
I know, all she needs
is someone to chat with.

29
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:15,653
Of course, to ease her trauma.

30
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:16,946
Right?

31
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:24,245
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

32
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:36,007
Agent Sianong and I strongly believe
that this is a Moraviano operative.

33
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:39,677
And we have very strong reasons to believe
that this person killed Attorney Redi

34
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:42,055
and carried out the Sinigang massacre.

35
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:44,766
We are dealing here
with a world-class assassin.

36
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:47,352
Based on our initial information,

37
00:03:47,435 --> 00:03:49,854
there is an emerging modus operandi.

38
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:59,239
I have a strong belief
that if we gave them a samurai sword,

39
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:01,658
they might even be better
than Kenshin Himura.

40
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,118
Like, Hiten Mitsurugi style.

41
00:04:04,869 --> 00:04:07,622
Exactly. That's why she is very dangerous.

42
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:10,708
But it's very important
that we identify her.

43
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:13,670
Because he or she knows

44
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:15,672
a lot of secrets
about the Moraviano group.

45
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:18,591
- Maybe it's Viktor Valtrovi himself.
- No, no, no.

46
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:20,301
Based on our information,

47
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:24,430
Viktor was in the hospital
during the Sinigang massacre.

48
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,849
And Donabel wouldn't talk either.

49
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,853
As a matter of fact,
Donabel is in Prague right now to lay low.

50
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,898
If he or she is as skilled
as a ninja or a samurai,

51
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:35,441
he or she must be Japanese?

52
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:40,947
What do you mean by interesting?

53
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,782
When we started investigating,

54
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:44,993
I reached out to my contact
in immigration.

55
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:47,245
I asked if they could alert us

56
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:51,124
of any Central Europeans
with a strong military background.

57
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:08,766
<i>If I'm not mistaken,</i>
<i>he is the head of Viktor's security.</i>

58
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,270
What's his background?

59
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,489
He became well-known
when he was deployed to Afghanistan,

60
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:26,075
where he extracted a high-value asset

61
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,869
right in the middle of Taliban territory.

62
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:30,913
The operation resulted
in the deaths of dozens of civilians.

63
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:33,791
He was dishonorably discharged
and was dubbed

64
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,251
Noční Řezník.

65
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:36,836
{\an8}<i>Or "The Butcher of the Night".</i>

66
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,684
Where did he go?

67
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,759
Love.

68
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:10,930
Why do you have
so many questions for Viktor?

69
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:14,976
Remember, they're victims, too.

70
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,602
Think about it.

71
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:19,063
Donabel was kidnapped.

72
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:21,941
Chiara is probably still traumatized.

73
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:28,990
I'm just frustrated, Tess.

74
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:33,536
It feels like there are
so many unanswered questions.

75
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:41,419
There are so many things
that just… just don't make sense.

76
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:44,797
For example, out of all people,

77
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:49,051
why do they get targeted by the gangs?

78
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:53,222
Our child was shot.

79
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:56,309
And then, it's like…
like nothing happened.

80
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:57,393
No investigation.

81
00:07:57,477 --> 00:08:01,856
We didn't even find out
who the suspect was

82
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:04,317
or who was behind all of this.

83
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,904
It reminded me of what you told me before,

84
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:12,200
that you had a bad feeling
when Mikoy met the Valtrovi family.

85
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:16,746
I was really worried that something
might happen to our child

86
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,831
if he accepted that job.

87
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:24,795
Maybe there's something…
There's something to what you felt.

88
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:27,048
If you ask me,

89
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,801
there's still so much we don't know.

90
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:34,055
I think Viktor has a serious enemy.

91
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:37,517
Just the truth.

92
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,937
So I can reassure myself
that Mikoy's life is safe now.

93
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,774
And that his life won't be at risk again.

94
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:47,026
Just remember, dear.

95
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,862
What we need to keep in mind,

96
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:52,406
whether it's dangerous or not,

97
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:57,078
is this is the life Mikoy chose.

98
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:01,749
This is what his heart chose.

99
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:17,139
I think he's just a father

100
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,850
who's concerned about
his child's well-being.

101
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:23,479
Of course, after what happened,
he'd want to know if Mikoy is really safe.

102
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,369
What does she want?

103
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:33,025
{\an8}MAREK VONDRAK
ATTORNEY GENERAL OF CZECH REPUBLIC

104
00:11:35,736 --> 00:11:36,946
Marek Vondrak?

105
00:11:47,289 --> 00:11:49,333
- <i>Chiara, my dear.</i>
- Yes, Mom?

106
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:50,459
I'm going shopping now.

107
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:52,837
Do you want me
to buy anything else for Mikoy?

108
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:55,464
Good thing I already made a list.

109
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:58,259
- We need to buy healthy food for Mikoy.
- Wait!

110
00:11:58,342 --> 00:11:59,718
- To aid his healing and recovery.
- Wait.

111
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:01,262
- Okay, game.
- All right.

112
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:03,556
There's just a few things I need, Mom.

113
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:06,016
To aid his body's ability
to repair tissue.

114
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,351
That's why we need protein.

115
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:08,269
- Okay, protein.
- We need

116
00:12:08,352 --> 00:12:10,354
chicken, eggs, fish,

117
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,648
- tofu, lentils, beans.
- Fish.

118
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:16,569
We also need to boost his vitamin C.

119
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:20,823
To boost collagen,
so his wounds can heal faster.

120
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:29,123
- We also need to boost his zinc and iron.
- Broccoli.

121
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:30,708
So we need to prepare meals

122
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:34,503
with spinach,
green leafy vegetables, nuts,

123
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:36,338
- and seeds.
- Nuts.

124
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:40,176
To help reduce inflammation,
we need healthy fats from avocado,

125
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:42,970
olive oil, or fatty fish, like salmon…

126
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:43,971
Wait, my dear.

127
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:48,184
- You already listed everything, right?
- Yes.

128
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:51,896
- Maybe just text it to me.
- Okay.

129
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:53,939
Or DM me.

130
00:12:54,023 --> 00:12:55,691
- Okay?
- Okay.

131
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:59,028
- Mom, just use the driver too.
- Okay, yes.

132
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:01,071
- Thank you very much!
- Bye!

133
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:40,194
<i>My sweetheart is really something.</i>

134
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:41,862
<i>I should be a good boy.</i>

135
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:43,405
<i>Or I might get hit.</i>

136
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:55,334
Sweetheart! What are you doing here?

137
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:56,877
I'm taking a bath.

138
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:59,463
Well, of course,
I'll help you take a bath.

139
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:03,509
No need. I can manage, love.

140
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:06,470
Sweetheart, you can barely move.

141
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:10,182
Are you sure?

142
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:11,600
Why? Don't you want me to?

143
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,187
Okay.

144
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:17,690
I'll do it.

145
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:48,345
- Ouch! Sweetheart, don't do that.
- What?

146
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,306
I'm ticklish there.

147
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:53,642
So you're ticklish.

148
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,311
You know what?

149
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:59,857
They say if a person is ticklish,

150
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:01,567
it means they lack something.

151
00:15:02,818 --> 00:15:03,819
Lack of what?

152
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,155
Lack of…

153
00:15:07,489 --> 00:15:08,657
Of what?

154
00:15:09,658 --> 00:15:11,076
You know!

155
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,120
Come on.

156
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:14,705
That thing.

157
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,263
Chiara, my dear.

158
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:38,354
Thank you very much.

159
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:43,484
Thank you so much for loving Mikoy.

160
00:15:45,361 --> 00:15:49,114
I really feel it these past few days.

161
00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:51,825
Just how you…

162
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:57,331
pour out so much love for my son.

163
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,962
Mom, I should be the one thanking you.

164
00:16:04,296 --> 00:16:06,340
Because I got to meet Mikoy.

165
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:11,470
I'm the truly blessed one
because I became part of your lives.

166
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:16,392
You're both blessed.

167
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:19,353
Because you're both good people.

168
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:24,400
I hope you're right, Mom.

169
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,860
Why do you say that?

170
00:16:27,611 --> 00:16:29,530
I know.

171
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:33,158
And I can feel your doubts.

172
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:36,495
Especially Daddy Mario.

173
00:16:36,578 --> 00:16:38,664
It shows on him.

174
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:42,668
I know you're wondering
whether this relationship

175
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:45,754
is right for Mikoy.

176
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:53,137
- Chiara.
- Mom, it's okay.

177
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:59,351
It's understandable
that you feel scared for Mikoy.

178
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:00,894
For your son.

179
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:04,148
Our worlds are very different.

180
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:12,573
it also comes with a lot of challenges.

181
00:17:12,656 --> 00:17:15,534
Sometimes those challenges

182
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:18,370
come from enemies,

183
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:22,082
opponents, and rivals.

184
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:30,883
Because of my Dad's high status in life.

185
00:17:38,515 --> 00:17:41,268
But I promise you, Mom.

186
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:46,023
No one will hurt Mikoy anymore.

187
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:50,110
I won't allow it.

188
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:53,906
I won't let anyone hurt the person I love.

189
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:08,879
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

190
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:11,215
I understand. I will fix this.

191
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:13,133
I'll take care of it.

192
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:16,678
Sir?

193
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:20,349
I just got a three-way call

194
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:23,602
from the Secretary of Justice

195
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:28,398
and a certain Attorney General
from the Czech Republic.

196
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:31,193
And I was reassuring them

197
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,696
that I didn't have any agent stupid enough

198
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:37,533
to kidnap a Czech citizen!

199
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,284
Technically, not kidnapping, sir.

200
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:43,163
Sir, we were trying
to bring him to the office,

201
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:47,209
but he resisted,
so, we kind of kidnapped him.

202
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:49,878
Kind of? Kind of kidnapped?

203
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:52,840
Are you kidding me?

204
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:57,553
We were just defending ourselves, sir.

205
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:01,515
Still, you have no right to hold him.

206
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:04,434
Sir, are you sure
we're going to release him?

207
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:15,028
But I saw him working for Viktor.

208
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:16,196
He is a Moraviano.

209
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,544
If we release him,

210
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:33,589
he'll just go back to Viktor,
and we'll be in deeper trouble.

211
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:41,847
You need to release him,
or we'll lose everything.

212
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:00,908
Is Mikoy okay now, Dad?

213
00:20:00,991 --> 00:20:01,992
<i>Don't worry.</i>

214
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:04,661
Your mom and Chiara
are taking good care of him.

215
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:07,998
I have a break tomorrow. I'll go there.

216
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:10,209
<i>Okay. I'll let your mom know.</i>

217
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,127
How are you?

218
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,712
I'm okay, Dad.

219
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:16,965
But can I ask something?

220
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,508
<i>Do you have any news about</i>

221
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:21,386
<i>who caused the trouble</i>
<i>at brother Mikoy's event?</i>

222
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:24,473
What did Mister Viktor say?

223
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:27,267
He said he already fixed everything.

224
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:29,645
But is Mikoy still safe?

225
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,480
Why do you ask that?

226
00:20:32,189 --> 00:20:34,107
I've been hearing things here, Dad.

227
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:37,736
You heard something? About what?

228
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:40,447
About Chiara's family.

229
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:43,659
That they're connected to syndicates.

230
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:45,202
Syndicates of what?

231
00:20:46,703 --> 00:20:48,205
Nothing, Dad.

232
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:51,375
Let's just ignore it.
It's probably just online gossip.

233
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:54,878
That's trending nowadays.
Engagement farming, clout chasers.

234
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:57,464
There are a lot of those now.
It doesn't seem true.

235
00:20:58,215 --> 00:20:59,841
It's probably just nonsense.

236
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:04,554
Angelito, don't listen
to those rumors, okay?

237
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:08,934
We'll take care of your brother.

238
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:10,143
Okay?

239
00:21:10,227 --> 00:21:11,603
Me personally.

240
00:21:12,187 --> 00:21:13,730
Okay, Dad. Love you, Dad.

241
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:16,900
<i>Send my love to Mom and Mikoy too.</i>

242
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:18,944
I love you too, my son.

243
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:20,279
Okay, bye-bye.

244
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:27,619
What are you doing there?
Have you been there long?

245
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:30,497
Sorry, Angelito.

246
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:34,793
I couldn't help but hear
your conversation with your father

247
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:36,586
about the syndicates.

248
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:42,426
But what if it's actually true
and not just gossip?

249
00:21:43,051 --> 00:21:46,638
I have a reliable source who says that

250
00:21:46,722 --> 00:21:50,017
the Valtrovi are really connected
to syndicates.

251
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:53,312
Don't joke like that. That's not funny.

252
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:55,647
Angelito, I'm not joking.

253
00:21:56,356 --> 00:21:58,066
You've gotten close to me,

254
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,402
and I feel like you deserve
this information.

255
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:04,114
Information? That you just read
from internet forums!

256
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:09,536
Remember that police officer
I told you about

257
00:22:09,619 --> 00:22:13,206
who I get information from,
my reliable source?

258
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:18,003
How can you be sure
that police officer is reliable?

259
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:20,005
Because he's my father.

260
00:22:20,088 --> 00:22:22,966
The Sinigang Syndicate
attacked the Valtrovis?

261
00:22:24,092 --> 00:22:25,510
Why would they do that?

262
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:28,972
They're not thinking!

263
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:32,267
The Moravianos
will definitely strike back!

264
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:36,396
The Valtrovis won't allow themselves
to be disrespected like that!

265
00:22:38,648 --> 00:22:39,900
Huh?

266
00:22:39,983 --> 00:22:42,652
Your dad is the reliable source
you're talking about?

267
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:45,489
Yes! And not just any police officer.

268
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:50,035
He's the director of the best
law enforcement agency in the country.

269
00:22:52,954 --> 00:22:58,043
The agency that investigates crimes
against Filipinos beyond borders!

270
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:01,463
Who else is more reliable than my father,

271
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,216
who is the police agency director?

272
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:05,759
Right? No one.

273
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:09,513
But listen,
I'm telling you this in confidence.

274
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:11,348
Don't ever spread it.

275
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:15,143
I just wanted to warn you
because we're friends!

276
00:23:16,394 --> 00:23:17,395
Warn me about what?

277
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:21,441
Of course, so you can tell
your brother to be careful.

278
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:24,486
Whether he likes it or not,
because of his girlfriend,

279
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:27,364
he's already entered
the dangerous world of syndicates.

280
00:23:27,447 --> 00:23:31,326
And that won't be the last time
his life gets threatened.

281
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,511
<i>She never refused my invitation.</i>

282
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:55,559
<i>Tell me why?</i>
<i>And be honest, or I'll kill you.</i>

283
00:24:18,498 --> 00:24:20,667
<i>Oh my goodness! Oh my God!</i>

284
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:35,015
{\an8}PAPA

285
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:14,429
<i>She thinks Mikoy is distracting you!</i>

286
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:58,598
It's because of Chiara.

287
00:25:58,682 --> 00:25:59,683
What's the problem with Chiara?

288
00:25:59,766 --> 00:26:03,812
<i>I talked to her a while ago,</i>
<i>and she's saying different things.</i>

289
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:09,025
She said that they have a lot of enemies
because they're rich.

290
00:26:09,109 --> 00:26:12,654
<i>I'm afraid for Mikoy.</i>
<i>He got into a dangerous life.</i>

291
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:16,366
Dad, I think you should know
something about Chiara's family.

